Thank you for your reading and observations

Regarding PdI, it's an abbreviation in Spanish for PoI, it was a detail that I accidentally left out during the proofreading and that was already corrected by Uncle Nicolini (Thanks Nico!)

About the format, I wrote this article on my computer, so I chose px for the images of both PoI, images aligned on the right), which looked good. Now I checked it on my cell phone and although the images look somewhat large, I don't think they will interrupt the reading to any great extent, I apologize for any inconvenience this may cause.

The article says that both entities  to both PoI because in universo and in spite of all the signals received, and that the actions would be consistent with the memories of both subjects (already deceased), the members of the Foundation have no way to confirm 100% that they really correspond to them (or to their memories, psychic echoes or their ghosts/spirits)

From a narrative point of view, I think there are times when it is better to hint than to say directly, to give the reader space to give interpretations to what he has read.







